Commentary Text: Lalit Yadav to Rahane, out Caught&Bowled!! What a catch! I was wondering why Lalit Yadav did not run Shivam Dube out. Dube was well out as he was backing up but Yadav has plucked a beaut with his right-hand. Even umpire Chris Gaffaney is impressed. He goes ooohhh. Rahane is stunned but has to walk back. He came down the track and drilled it low and flat to the right of Yadav, who had Dube in the way too, but hangs on and ensures the ball does not touch the ground as he lands. Outstanding and now the anchor of CSK is gone. DC on top. Rahane c and b Lalit Yadav 21(20) [4s-2]
